DETAILS OF EACH CAPACITY PARAMETER OF SSD

Why can't the SATA SSD be recognized after installation? When using an SSD for the first time, it needs to be formatted and partitioned first. You can use "Disk Management Tool" to format and partition the SSD, and then use it in "Windows Explorer". Why is the actual capacity of SSD smaller than the advertised capacity? Because the manufacturer's calculation method is 1TB=1000MB=1000000KB=1000000000B, and the computer system's calculation method is 1TB=1024MB=1024*1024KB=1024*1024*1024B, so the capacity you see is 1TB=(1000*1000*1000)/(1024*1024*1024)TB≈0.93TB. How to copy data to a new SSD? We have launched the latest FANXIANG SSD Toolbox, which can read the running status of SSDs. At the same time, it also has disk cloning and system migration functions (Note: this operation will delete all data on the target hard drive). What does the product packaging contain? "After purchasing the product you will receive: 1 * 2.5-inch SATA SSD, 1 * product box Note: The product does not include a SATA cable. If needed, please purchase separately. Thank you." How can I know if this product is compatible with my computer? For a 2.5" SATA SSD, as long as your computer has a SATA interface or previously used either a mechanical hard drive or a solid-state drive, you can use this SSD

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This HD is less expensive, and for that reason I felt nervous purchasing it. After arrival, I plug it into a Video Recorder and it formats and records OK. Sigh of relief.HOWEVER, I attach it to my computer via a Sabrent USB 3.1 2.5" SSD Cable Adapter - EC-SS31 purchased elsewhere, and the computer did NOT FULLY RECOGNIZE IT. Additionally, I can't initialize via MMC in Windows 11 because a terse error appears leaving me hanging. When I check the Windows systray, it shows the device for detaching but does not assign a drive letter. So I boot into Ubuntu 22.04 Linux and similar issue. GParted does not even recognize the drive. Attaching the drive to the computer is critical for transferring files from the Video Recorder so that I can edit them on the computer.Luckily I also have a Wavlink USB 3 2.5" HD case. Trying the drive with this will possibly eliminate any issue with the Sabrent adapter.The drive immediately is recognized with the Wavlink, fully initialized, formatted and pops up in the operating system and transfers files.Just because the device is inexpensive does not mean it is no good. If possible, properly check and eliminate all other variables before calling support or returning.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Inital testing indicates this is good given the price point but don't fill it up
reviews.reviewText: I received the 1TB model new in box. I ran volume recovery on it out of curiosity and found an NTFS volume labeled "SSD_7" file: "System Volume Information/WPSettings.dat" Unexpected and curious. Here's the hexdump:0000000 000c 0000 6954 7a1b 4da3 a85f000000c Model Number: Fanxiang S101 1TB Serial Number: MX_00000000000024267 Firmware Revision: SN14130 device size with M = 1024*1024: 976762 MBytes device size with M = 1000*1000: 1024209 MBytes (1024 GB)I wrote a gpt label, formatted ext4 without a journal and ran f3 on it:Average writing speed: 133.20 MB/s Data OK: 938.80 GB (1968814104 sectors)Data LOST: 0.00 Byte (0 sectors) Corrupted: 0.00 Byte (0 sectors) Slightly changed: 0.00 Byte (0 sectors) Overwritten: 0.00 Byte (0 sectors)Average reading speed: 410.50 MB/sSeems real. Adequate performance even if a bit slow on the writes. Note the write speed was faster when it was less than half full. About 250MB/s at 17% full and about 90 MB.s at 85% full. I've posted the total average write speed when filling the drive with f3write above.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really Fast, keeps up with fastest competition
reviews.reviewText: A large network company controller uses a Intel Pentium N5030 mother board for a network controller as it contains a M.2 2280 storage but it had an unloaded (empty) SATA 2.5 drive bay. I dropped in a Samsung EVO drive into the slot and benchmarked with Win11 internal app "winsat disk", and happiness with a 25% drive full and 250GB test file. When the FanXiang S102 Pro SATA III was dropped in, it tested to be 18% faster writing, same read, than the Samsung EVO, the Samsung supposed to be the fastest drive sold. BUT the FanXiang S102 Pro tested to be faster and is less than half the price. Given limited testing only 0.25TB file an 25% full. Didn't find the ability to to hardware encrypt but don't care as I use software OS encryption. It's used to store Virtual OS and containers and years of network log files so it doesn't get used a lot. The FanXiang S102 uses SLC as core and cache and some 25% TLC as long term store and Samsung uses DRAM as cache and TLC for store. Understand why Samsung runs hotter but it also should be faster but is not. Buy the 102 Pro over the 101 because it is just slightly more expensive but faster than the best rated Samsung in my application. I'm a silicon design engineer and fascinated by design choices. I really like the FanXiang S102 Pro design implementation. Save money and buy this design. Sometimes good designs need to be rewarded even if they come from a smaller company.
